(367, 1, '2014-12-07 11:03:09', '2014-12-07 11:03:09', '<strong>Encapsulation </strong>: encapsulation is the concept that is use to make the difference between interface and implementation. It implemented by the private keyword this concept is also known as data hiding.\r\n• Encapsulation is to ascertain that each part of an application is seperate and doesn''t interfere with any others.\r\n\r\n• When defining a property in a class, you must specify whether it''s public, private, or protected.\r\n\r\n• Public properties are available to all parts of a PHP script, both inside and outside the class definition, and their values can be changed in the same way as any variable.\r\n\r\n• Protected and private properties are invisible from external scripts, so they cannot be changed arbitrarily.\r\n\r\nExample\r\nIn below example you can see the function display is private method of class <strong>Encapsulation </strong> if you create the object of class <strong>Encapsulation </strong> and access the function <strong>display</strong> then fatal error will show on the screen.because the private method and variable is not accessible on the outside of class then question is there how we can access the function <strong>display</strong>.firstly you have to create another public function for access your all private member you can see in below example i have created function <strong>callprivatemenber</strong> and i am calling the function <strong>display </strong> inside the <strong>callprivatemenber </strong>function.Here we can see the function display is not directly called on the object level it means the function display is encapsulated function of the class.\r\nclass Encapsulation  \r\n    {  \r\n        private function display()  \r\n        {  \r\n            echo " This is private Function";  \r\n        }  \r\n        public function callprivatemenber()\r\n	{\r\n		  $this->display();\r\n	}  \r\n\r\n      \r\n    }  \r\n    class Test extends Encapsulation  \r\n    {  \r\n        function display()  \r\n        {  \r\n            echo "This is sub class";  \r\n        }  \r\n    }  \r\n    $obj=new Encapsulation();  \r\n    $obj->display();\r\n    $obj->callprivatemenber();\r\n\r\nOutput : Fatal error: Call to private method Encapsulation::display()', 'Encapsulation in php', ' encapsulation is the concept that is user to make the difference between interface and implementation. It implemented by the private keyword this concept is also known as data hiding', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'encapsulation-php', '', '', '2014-12-27 02:08:16', '2014-12-27 02:08:16', '', 0, 'http://itsterling.com/?p=367', 0, 'post', '', 1),
